                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d897">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7223</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Edwards</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-17T09:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1916, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>First passenger train in ten days arrived from Casas Grandes, Pearson and the
                    Mormon Colony District at ten last night bringing about twenty-five Americans
                    among whom were dozen women and children. They report having been fully informed
                    in due time of the massacre at Santa Ysabel. A number who arrived came on
                    business and expect to return. They report conditions to them <pb facs="0737"
                        n="661" xml:id="pg_661"/> unalarming as they consider the garrisons at towns
                    mentioned quite sufficient to protect their people. This consul will, however,
                    insist on their sending their women and children to place of safety. The
                    garrison at Casas Grandes numbers 400 and at Pearson 300. These figures are
                    given by Americans of Madera. Little is known that is reliable but nothing of an
                    unalarming nature reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
